It's definitely a scam. Few months ago  my sister was told the same thing  ask to sell all shares and and wait for the call to buy hsi. stock recommended by him . They normally pump up a stock a few days earlier  and on that particular day  they will what'sapp you to buy their "high prices stock" just before noon. Print screen the proof that you bought. After lunch they then  start to dump the share in the market. She soon realised and sold the next day   lost about 1k.

Thanks for the comment.To all  please refrain from taking advice from anyone who you don’t know and recommend Hsi stocks to you.A Frd of my fell for it and only shared with me when he lost s$250k.Initially was a winning streak and won around s$20k then “trusted” and dumped in almost s$250k then next day gapped down and lost 90% of the value.Kindly be prudent and don’t greed. ☺️
